<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n47141f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n47" href="#n47141f">N47 (VI.B.40)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n47all.htm#n47141f"> 141(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sahu</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">9. The <i>sahu</i> <font color="green">[image]</font>, or spiritual body, which formed the habitation of the soul. It sprang from the material body, through the prayers which were said, and the ceremonies which were performed at the tomb and elsewhere by duly appointed and properly qualified priests, and was lasting and incorruptible. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD3"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd Ed (1909) lxiv [The constituent parts of man physically, mentally, and spiritually]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
